summary: Aisle 6 Remix  Fic summary: I feel like….someone’s watching me. Eve looks up from the two flimsy boxes in her hands (microwave...
caption:
Aisle 6 Remix 

Fic summary:

I feel like….someone’s watching me.

Eve looks up from the two flimsy boxes in her hands (microwave stroganoff and frozen gluten-free shepherd’s pie) to see that someone was indeed looking intensely her way. A woman stands a few feet away, cart halted, staring right at her. Young, sickly pale, hair in disarray, clung sweaty to her forehead.

Eve figures she should probably address this situation.


|| One overthinking gay’s remix of the best queer spy vs spy romance on film, if bits of Season 1 were smushed with bits of Season 2 and it all started with a meetcute in a grocery aisle.

Chapter 01: Knife me, rob me, creep up in my sleep

|| In this universe, here’s where it begins. It’s a good thing Eve’s a terrible cook.

Click here or on the header above to give it a read! 

Hello from me, the writer:

Hey! It’s 2k19 and fuck it I’m finally writing fanfic. It’s bananas I haven’t before but I feel good that a show as completely slick, smart, sexy, and super fucking gay as Killing Eve was the one to pull me in finally. 

Here’s Fic #1, Ch 1 for me. I had this thought after 2.02 dropped, kept thinking about it, thought it had potential and eventually decided to think it into existence.

And yeah, I’m a very extra gay who enjoys making little graphics so I did decide on a whim to make chapter graphics. I hope someone enjoys this but if not who am I kidding I did it for me. The plan’s to hopefully do it every chapter.

The feedback I’ve received so far has been so positive and kind, I’m super happy about it?? Thank you to everyone who gives it a read! Please feel free to hit me up here or in the comments if you’ve got anything you’d like to say or ask.

Plenty chapters ahead, the next to come Monday <3

summary: For several times my mother asked me if I was watching Killing Eve. I wasn't necessary interested by the series. As I called her...
body:
For several times my mother asked me if I was watching Killing Eve. I wasn’t necessary interested by the series. As I called her last Sunday for mother’s day, she talked to me again about the series. So I decided to watch it.

By Monday I had already seen the whole first season. And Tuesday night I was already at episode six of season two, like everyone else.

So yeah I became an fan. Especially of Villanelle. She’s more fun than Dexter. Jodie Comer is a great actress, she’s really good in that character.
